Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
write_category_summary(25.10)                    write_category_summary(25.10)

Name
       write_category_summary  -  Writes  a text file containing the following
       information

Syntax
       write_category_summary

       [-help]

       -report <string>

       [[-ascend | -descend ]

       [-byTNS | -byWNS ]]

       [-csv | {-no_frame_fix_width [-no_split]}]

       Writes a text file containing the following information.

              * Category name

              * Total number of paths

              * Number of passing paths

              * Number of failing paths

              * Worst negative slack

              * Total negative slack

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each write_category_summary parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man write_category_summary

       -ascend
              Specifies that the report in ascending order, should specify op-
              tion -byTNS or -byWNS.

       -byTNS The TNS value specified by the sorting key  through  the  option
              -ascend or -descend.

       -byWNS The  WNS  value  specified by the sorting key through the option
              -ascend or -descend.

       -csv   Reports entries in csv format.

       -descend
              Specifies that the report in descending  order,  should  specify
              option -byTNS or -byWNS.

       -no_frame_fix_width
              Specifies that the table columns have a fixed minimum width, but
              no maximum width (the data does not wrap). Column data that fits
              within  the column's minimum width will left-justify and pad its
              location to fill the specified column space.

              Column data that is longer than the column's minimum width  will
              take  as much space in the table as needed. If a column is over-
              written by the data from the preceding column, its data will be-
              gin on a new line at the correct column location.

       -no_split
              Specifies that each column follows the preceding column  without
              splitting  to a new line, if the data in one column overruns the
              next column. The wrapping behavior for data is controlled by the
              size of the display window.

              This format is useful for machine parsing the report.

              Note: You must specify -no_frame_fix_width in order to use  this
              parameter.

       -report fileName
              Specifies the name of the category report file.

              Default: category.rpt

Examples
       The following command writes a category summary file category.rpt:

       write_category_summary -report category.rpt

